    "updated_at": "2016-08-04T03:21:09Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I don't think this is the correct fix. It's confusing that some troops aren't selectable. Numerous selection attempts are needed to move troops into a transport. The proper solution (and I think the original RA did this) is to not have the engineers move when given an attack order. You have a group huddled together and you give an attack order. Those that can attack go running after the target. Those that can't remain idle. \n"
